Assassins have turned the village of Kalkuta in Juja, Kiambu county, into a dumpsite.Residents complained on Wednesday three bodies have been dumped in the area in three months.They spoke days after the body of Kiru Boys High School principal Solomon Mwangi was found in a thicket in Karuntuma coffee farm. His widow is held in the torture slaying. The bodies are usually stuffed in sacks. Two months ago the body of a primary school child was found a few metres from the principal s body, resident James Mwangi said. Criminals are making our village a dumpsite for their victims. Our children are traumatised ... the path to school passes through the bushes [where bodies were found]. 